metadata.name: All The Way #34
metadata.description:
"All the Way" is a visually stunning and dynamic generative art piece that is sure to make a striking addition to any art collection. Created using the programming language p5js, this artwork is truly one of a kind and cannot be replicated.

The vibrant colors, fluid shapes, and dynamic movement in "All the Way" make it an ideal centerpiece for any space. The constantly shifting shapes and colors create a sense of energy and motion that will draw the eye and captivate the viewer. This piece is perfect for anyone who loves abstract art or is looking for something unique and eye-catching to add to their collection.

Additionally, the theme of "All the Way" is one that is sure to resonate with many people. The artwork represents the flow of life, the power of creativity, and the endless possibilities that exist in the world around us. This makes it an ideal choice for anyone who values personal growth, exploration, and a sense of adventure.

Whether you're an art collector, an art enthusiast, or simply someone who appreciates beautiful and thought-provoking art, "All the Way" is a must-have addition to your collection. With its dynamic and abstract style, this piece is sure to spark conversations and inspire new ideas. Don't miss out on the chance to own a truly unique and captivating artwork that you will enjoy for years to come!

To save image press "s"
To save image in high quality add &print=2 or &print=3 in the live URL then press "s".

Note: Image can take a minute to render.

Created using p5js and p5js pattern
Created By Winston

metadata.name: The Face We Had #282
metadata.description:
The Face We Had is a series of generative, moving sculptures attempting to express the artists personal thoughts, experiences and inclinations related to meditative and altered states of consciousness. In a non-descriptive way, the piece aims to reflect the always changing nature of mind through patterns of movement and assemblages of form, color and organic shapes, endlessly revolving around a perceived point of origin.  

Although not intended as literal depictions, the elements interact in a way that could be interpreted as dance-like interactions between thought patterns, mental energy, feelings, fragments of memories and layers of personal identity. 



Interactive features:

space - pause/play
w - wireframe view
d - debug view (compute textures)
s - save screenshot

metadata.name: Skravert #258
metadata.description:
‘Skravert’ - Norwegian, verb, past tense. ‘The act of filling an area with lines; to shade an area’.

Skravert is a series of 320 sketches, each capturing the texture and feel of a material residing somewhere between cardboard and woolen rugs. The project is centred around rectangle subdivision and a line drawing algorithm, giving each piece its own unique expression when combined with a selection of 28 different color  palettes.  

Original artwork by perkwerk * made with p5.js * 2021

metadata.name: tr4ns4ctions #177
metadata.description:
Tr4ns4ctions is a series of real-time animations that use pixels to create an abstraction of the movement of values. The pixels are constantly rearranging, being transferred from offer to taker, liquify, appear and disappear. They are forming endless compositions, sometimes intransparent or with strange spins.

The level of abstraction has been set to a 2x pixel size and the color palette of the NES with 12 different color modes. 16 pixel patterns serve as the fundamental building blocks and a simplex noise field determines the direction of movement.

click || space => pause/unpause

View all tr4ns4ctions at https://tr4ns4ctions.com

Kim Asendorf, 2022

metadata.name: Tangentum #75
metadata.description:
We live in a multiverse: an infinite-dimensional space of variants. Everything exists here. Everything is possible. Each subset of a multiverse has its own unique laws of physics, a set of rules, and its own distinct features.

Tangentum creates a projection of a random multiverse subset to a 2-dimensional plane. Each variation is a unique representation of the force field, that exists somewhere at some point in time.

This work starts a series of my visual exploration of functions, continuity, and boundedness, and I would love to share it with you.


Please use fullscreen or download artwork in high resolution for a better viewing experience.

Tested with Chrome 107, Safari, and Firefox. Chrome is recommended, other browsers are slower on this artwork.

Saving with high and ultra-high resolution may take a while, please be patient.


Made with love and p5js


Controls in fullscreen:
[1] - save PNG 2700 x 1800
[2] - save PNG 5400 x 3800
[3] - save PNG 10800 x 7600
[4] - save PNG 16200 x 11400
